  "summary": "This build presents a clean, restrained todo interface with strong consistency, clear empty-state guidance, and an obvious dismissible error banner that communicates API issues well. Visual hierarchy is solid, with a clear title, simple form, and subdued secondary text, while visible focus styling and basic labeling support accessible interaction. The main weaknesses are limited error prevention and user control: the add form disables native validation, advanced efficiency features are absent, and loading feedback appears to rely mostly on subtle opacity changes. Exposing the technical \"API base\" control also makes the experience feel more developer-facing than everyday-task-oriented.",
